{
  "local_port": 45042,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best date cake recipes?",
  "response": "Date cakes are delicious and offer a unique sweetness that comes from the natural sugars in dates. Here are a couple of top-rated date cake recipes that you might enjoy trying at home:\n\n### 1. Sticky Date Cake with Toffee Sauce\n\n#### Ingredients:\n- **For the Cake:**\n  - 1 cup dates, pitted and chopped\n  - 1 1/4 cups boiling water\n  - 1 tsp baking soda\n  - 1/4 cup unsalted butter, softened\n  - 3/4 cup brown sugar\n  - 2 large eggs\n  - 1 tsp vanilla extract\n  - 1 1/3 cups all-purpose flour\n  - 1 tsp baking powder\n  - 1/4 tsp salt\n\n- **For the Toffee Sauce:**\n  - 1/2 cup unsalted butter\n  - 1 cup heavy cream\n  - 1 cup brown sugar\n  - Pinch of salt\n\n#### Instructions:\n1. **Preheat Oven:** Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease and flour a 9-inch round cake pan.\n2. **Prepare Dates:** Place the chopped dates in a bowl and pour boiling water over them. Stir in the baking soda and let sit for about 10 minutes until the dates are softened.\n3. **Mix Batter:** In a separate bowl, cream together the butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time, followed by the vanilla extract. Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Gradually mix the dry ingredients into the butter mixture. Fold in the date mixture until well combined.\n4. **Bake:** Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for about 30-35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n5. **Make Toffee Sauce:** While the cake is baking, prepare the toffee sauce. In a saucepan, combine the butter, heavy cream, brown sugar, and a pinch of salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the sugar has dissolved and the sauce is smooth and slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.\n6. **Serve:** Let the cake cool slightly before serving. Poke holes in the top of the cake with a skewer and pour about half of the toffee sauce over the cake, allowing it to soak in. Serve slices of cake with additional warm toffee sauce drizzled on top.\n\n### 2. Date and Nut Cake\n\n#### Ingredients:\n- 1 cup dates, pitted and chopped\n- 1 cup boiling water\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 1/2 cup unsalted butter, softened\n- 1 cup granulated sugar\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1 cup chopped walnuts or pecans\n\n#### Instructions:\n1. **Preheat Oven:** Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease and flour a 9x5 inch loaf pan.\n2. **Prepare Dates:** Place the chopped dates in a bowl and pour boiling water over them. Stir in the baking soda and let sit for about 10 minutes until the dates are softened.\n3. **Mix Batter:** In a separate bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time, followed by the vanilla extract. Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Gradually mix the dry ingredients into the butter mixture. Fold in the date mixture and chopped nuts until well combined.\n4. **Bake:** Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan and bake for about 50-60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n5. **Cool and Serve:** Allow the cake to cool in the pan for about 10 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely. Slice and serve.\n\nThese recipes showcase the rich, caramel-like flavor of dates in a moist and delicious cake. Enjoy experimenting with them!",
